Codefire kickstart Rails App

Before you start:
Make sure the project repo has been setup on Github and your account has been added as a collaborator.

Usage:
1. $ git clone git@github.com:codefire/kickstart.git $APP_NAME
2. $ cd $APP_NAME; bundle install
3. $ sed s/kickstart/$APP_NAME/g < config/database.yml.example > config/database.yml 
4. edit config/database.yml username/password to suit your dev setup.
5. $ sed s/kickstart/$APP_NAME/g < config/initializers/session_store.rb > config/initializers/session_store.rb
6. $ git remote set-url origin git@github.com:codefire/$APP_NAME.git
7. $ git push origin master

If you've done all that right, you should have your new kickstart app committed to the project repo. You can now go ahead and edit the deploy.rb file for Capistrano.

 $ sed s/kickstart/$APP_NAME/g < config/deploy.rb.example > config/deploy.rb